Native to Brooklyn, Ruby is a reiki practitioner as well as a licensed massage therapist.  She received her reiki training from her father, and her masage training form the Swedish Institute of Health Sciences in NYC.  She is currently continuing her education with craniosacral therapy, and is always interested in exploring new ways to use herbs for healing and relaxation.  Ruby is delighted to work with the Brooklyn Herborium, where she can combine so many of her passions with such lovely people.  Combining reiki with elements of massage, hot stone therapy and reflexology, as well as the beautiful oils we all know and love from the Brooklyn Herborium, Ruby strives to tailor each session to her client's needs. Come, relax, and leave feeling deeply nurtured.

30 Minute Massage
Incredible relaxation massage to the head, neck, shoulders and face.  Make it 60 minutes {$100} to include hand and foot reflexology.  These treatments have the option to include hot stones and aromatherapy as well. {$60}


Reiki Treatment {60 minutes}
Reiki is an ancient method of physical and spiritual healing. It has been effective in helping virtually every known malady. Here, Reiki is used as a key element of therapeutic massage and can dramatically improve physical and mental well being through loving wisdom.  Many people find this work most beneficial when done once a week for 3-5 weeks, but one can schedule a single session whenever it feels needed. Reiki is also a great way to nurture oneself during pregnancy and leading up to birth. Babies are pure energy and love reiki.
{$100}

Deep Spirit Reiki Treatment {90 minutes}
Reiki healing combined with other modalities to enhance the relaxation experience.  Can include massage of the head, neck, shoulders and face, hand and foot reflexology, hot stone therapy, and aromatherapy.  These can be mixed and employed to best suit a client's needs. Special treatment will be given to any areas which need attention.
{$150}

For more about Reiki:
What is Reiki??
Reiki is a healing treatment that is beneficial to your energy.   A lot of people use the word "energy", what does it imply?  There is only one energy, and it animates and flows through all things, you, me, a flower, a stone, a star, a galaxy.  This energy needs clear smooth channels to flow through, and when it does, you feel your best; balanced with a clear head, things seem to work with less effort and you can be flexible and open. But, when something disturbs the flow of this energy, a barrier is placed in it's path, things can become difficult.  There can be sickness, depression, a feeling of being "stuck" or "off".   A barrier can be as seemingly insignificant as a little argument with your partner or co-worker, or it can be a major life event.  Sometimes these things work themselves out, but when things persist we need help to bring ourselves back to our balance.  This is where energetic healing can be a great help.  By allowing our systems to relax, as happens during reiki, we allow healing and realignment to occur.
Reiki is a tradition of energetic healing developed in Japan.  The reiki practitioner acts as a conduit to let the energy of the universe flow to the recipient, helping them to clear their energetic pathways to get back to that open, balanced place.  This energy is intelligent, it knows where it needs to go, where it's purpose is.  During a treatment, a practitioner may be draw to one area of the body or another, but it is this intelligent energy that is doing the work, not them.  Because of this, reiki can do no harm.  It is gentle enough to accompany any other treatments or therapies one may be receiving.  It can be employed for someone who is "feeling blue", someone dealing with a chronic or fatal disease, or anyone in between.  Some people get reiki cause it just feels great, and they are better for receiving it on a regular basis. 
What is a reiki session like?
A reiki session can be vastly different depending on who you get it from.  When I, Ruby, do reiki, it is with a very soft touch.  Sometimes the work is hands on, sometimes hands off. The recipient lays comfortably on a treatment table fully clothed, or undressed under a sheet if they are also receiving a massage.  Throughout the session I hold the head, the hands, the feet, as well as lay my hands on the body over energetic centers.  Breasts and groin are never touched.  There is no oil used on the skin (unless the session is including massage), but I do sometimes use essential oils as I see fit or as my client requests.  At the beginning and end of the session there can be some gentle rocking of the body, traction of the head and neck or of the legs to loosen the body. A short massage to the face or scalp can be helpful so that the recipient can leave the day behind and bring their attention into their body.  Some people chose to speak about what they feel or see during reiki, some choose not to, whatever is most comfortable to the client is honored.  It is important that anything that comes up is acknowledged, but the way that is done is different for everybody.  At the end of a reiki session most people feel very relaxed, sometimes sleepy but sometimes energized, always with a smile on their face.

